**Addendum 1:** After experimentation and several related accidents, it has been confirmed that the abnormal characteristics of SCP-CN-1921 can affect the concept of sealing. If SCP-CN-1921 can contact the concept's carrier for an extended period of time, it will strengthen the related concepts, making them hard to destroy. The Object Class has been updated to Thaumiel; the object has been filed as part of a proposal to strengthen containment procedures.

**Addendum 2:** A filled Sky Wall hole in [[[SCP-CN-1997]]]-1 showed signs of instability two days after routine reinforcement in April 2012. The preparatory capacity required to carry out reinforcement again in a short period of time exceeded the capacity of the Sky Wall Maintenance Committee. Following approval by O5-9, SCP-CN-1921 was moved to the restoration ceremony site for reinforcement, which was explained to internal staff as part of Foundation-Zhujihui goodwill exchange activities. When SCP-CN-1921 was placed at the venue, the spatial instability of the repaired section quickly stopped, and EVE fluctuations returned to a stable level.

Sector-1921 was subsequently established around the ceremony site for SCP-CN-1921 to live in until the Sky Wall hole was completely repaired. Due to the location, it was explained to the public as "the new exhibition hall of the reconstructed Hong Shing Ocean Park" to cover up SCP-CN-1921's presence.

**Addendum 3:**
> This little pup is very impressive -- not because it blew up a canned surströmming that my men brought in, but its suppression ability. The moment it climbed on the mountain of thaumaturgic alloys and divine energy ores, the undulated twisting Sky Wall calmed down immediately, and all the cracks from which energy was leaking closed up.
> 
> It is a living Ruyi Bang, a crawling seal, not just as in the animal, but as in "to seal away", suppressing all unrest wherever it goes.
> 
> But its might makes me worry about one thing:
> 
> The seals that it is reinforcing will loosen when it is moved away. How about where it was found? Is there something suppressed in Qinghai Lake?
> 
> [[[scp-4290|Have we loosened some shackles without even realizing it?]]]
> 
> //Malekith Phoenix//
> //Director, Sector-1921//
